<h1>Pipeline Building Overview</h1>

<p><strong>Pipeline:</strong> <% $pipeline_builder->getName %></p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> <% $pipeline_builder->getDescription %></p>

<p>Hover your mouse over a module to view a desciption of the programs within
that module.  Please use the Pipeline Customization Tools menu on the right to 
modify the pipeline.</p>

<& draw_workflow.mas, pipeline_builder => $pipeline_builder &>

<& right_menu.mas, pipeline_builder => $pipeline_builder &>

<div id="WT" class="hidden documentation pipelineView"><div id="WT_arrow_right"></div><div id="WT_close_right"><span>Walkthrough</span><a class="btn-hide" href="#">Close</a></div><div id="WT_copy">
<p>This is the Pipeline Building Overview page.  Using the toolbox 
you can edit your pipelines details, view inputs and outputs, select 
which programs to run, edit program paramenters, finalize your 
pipeline, or cancel the building process.</p>

<p>Hovering over the image of the pipeline will bring up a tip.  
This tip contains a description of what is executed in that 
module.  Green boxes are active modules which will be run, 
red boxes are inactive modules which will not be run, 
grey boxes are required modules which must be run, and 
yellow boxes indicate only a portion of that module 
is being executed.</p>

<p>To continue with this tutorial choose <span class="highlight">
Select Programs to Run</span> from the toolbox.</p>

<p>Once you are done customizing your pipeline use the 
toolbox and choose <span class="highlight">Finalize Pipeline<span class="highlight">.</p>
</div></div>
